In this article, it is stated that the President met with nurses to discuss the importance of commonsense immigration reform. The President emphasized that reforming the legal immigration system can benefit public health by allowing immigrant nurses to stay in the United States legally and improve their skills. He also stressed the need for Congress to take action and pass immigration reform, criticizing House Republicans for delaying the process. The President and the nurses agreed that immigration reform would benefit communities and boost the economy. The nurses were thanked for their leadership and contributions to their communities.